On Religious Freedom Day, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation celebrating the various faiths that exist in the United States and honoring the 232nd anniversary of the passing of the Virginia Statute of Religious Freedom. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of religious freedom as a sacred right granted by God, not the government. It also highlights the need to protect religious freedom and combat any encroachments on this fundamental freedom. President Trump affirms the United States' commitment to promoting religious freedom globally and condemns acts of extremism, terrorism, and violence against people of faith. The proclamation calls on all Americans to commemorate Religious Freedom Day and work towards securing and preserving religious liberty both domestically and internationally.